   SIBLEY-COLUMN _ You never know what the mail will bring from
antiques dealer Harvey Bourland. I was still mulling over his
campaign to put a watermelon on the Georgia flag and, I think, also
on the Georgia capitol dome, when he came through with a couple of
other projects. One of them, called Planned Planthood Society,
purports to save all those plants some of us bring home from the
nursery and don't get around to setting out. (Sibley, Atlanta
