the boy's 200-yard freestyle relay, she cried. But, of course,
Terri Harmon cries at ``the first everything.'' The first time some
kid unknowingly hurt her son's feelings. The first time a doctor
told her he was not quite right. And today, when a young mother,
maybe even a woman who's pregnant with a Down syndrome baby, calls
to inquire about this or that, she cannot wait to tell them the
absolute, positive truth: Frank is fabulous. (Minor, Palm Beach
Post) MOVED.
