   CUBA-LOPEZ _ HAVANA _ Zoila Lopez put her faith in the Cuban
revolution for 38 years. She cut cane during sugar harvests. She
donated blood for Cuba's internationalist soldiers. She dutifully
taught her son that God didn't exist. Her allegiance was rewarded
by membership in the PCC, the Cuban Communist Party, an honor
reserved for the revolutionary vanguard. Then the former teacher
and bookkeeper found God. (Douthat, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SANIBEL-SHELLS _ SANIBEL, Fla. _ I want to be first. I want to
pick up what treasures the sea has sprinkled along the shoreline
during the night. I am a shell hunter and, for me, the hunt has
begun. What better place than an island with more than 20 miles of
beaches and 300 species of shells? Sanibel Island is rated by some
as the third-best shelling place in the world, outranked only by
Australia's Great Barrier Reef and the Philippine islands.
(Pallesen, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
