<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Thursday, July 23, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Tina May at (206) 448-8355.
</P>
<P>
   ECONOMY-COLUMN-RAMSEY (Undated) High wages are the birthright of
Americans. But in a world economy, says Professor Michael Porter of
Harvard Business School, high wages have to be earned.
Increasingly, he argues, they have to be earned through innovation
_ by offering new things that can be sold at top prices.
</P>
<P>
   By Bruce Ramsey. (story will move in the ``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   TV-CRITICS (Pasadena, Calif.) From the TV critics' press tour in
Pasadena.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (story will move in the ``e'' category)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-22-98 1256EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
