<P>
   KITCHEN-HELP (Ferrisburg, Vt.) -- At a resort on Lake Champlain,
off-duty employees spend the summer in an after-hours world of
their own. By Nathan Cobb. 1700 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   FUTURE-SEERS (Undated) _ On the eve of the millenium and in the
midst of a historic technological revolution, everyone wants a
glimpse of the future. So the ranks of the seers are swelling with
professors, venture-capital consultants, and high-tech nerds. By
Adam Pertman. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   BEAM-COLUMN (Undated) -- Ah, the curse of homonomeia! What is to
be done? Stamp bar codes on infants at birth? By Alex Beam.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MAGAZINE-REVIEW (Undated) _ Stars, pols, flakes, and
curmudgeons. By Don Aucoin.
