   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GAYS (Washington) _ As the House prepares to vote on two
Republican-sponsored anti-gay measures, the National Organization
for Women stages a march outside the Capitol calling for an end to
homophobia. NOW President Patricia Ireland says passage of such
bills would make Republicans look ``mean and hateful.'' By JUDY
HOLLAND.
</P>
<P>
   FILIPINO-VETS (Washington) _ Filipino veterans urge Congress to
grant full benefits to the surviving members of the Philippine army
who fought alongside U.S. forces during World War II. By NICOLE
TSONG.
</P>
<P>
   DAVIS-CALIFORNIA (Washington) _ California Lt. Gov. Gray Davis,
who is running for state governor, visits Washington seeking
Democratic support in his bid to defeat his Republican opponent,
State Attorney General Dan Lungren, this November. By DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   For Sunday:
</P>
