   &UR; NATIONAL GENERAL &LR;  (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   OBIT-SHEPARD (Undated) _ Alan Shepard, one of America's original
seven astronauts and the first, in 1961, to ride a rocket into
space, has died. Shepard, 74, who later went to the moon and hit a
golf ball there, died at his home in Monterey, Calif. By John Noble
Wilford.
</P>
<P>
   With sidebars as appropriate.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON &LR;  (``w'' code)
