bills. By Katharine Q. Seelye.
</P>
<P>
   AIR-FORCE-CONFIRM (Washington) _ Senate committee votes on Daryl
Jones, nominee for secretary of the Air Force. By Eric Schmitt.
</P>
<P>
   ENERGY-CONFIRM (Washington) _ Senate Committee holds
confirmation hearing on Richardson to be Energy secretary. By
Matthew L. Wald.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SCIENCE &LR;  (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-CLONED-MICE (Undated) _ In the nearly 17 months since
biologists in Scotland said they cloned an adult sheep, ethicists
have vigorously debated where it would all lead. And a coterie of
skeptics asked if it had happened at all and, if so, when would the
world see a second clone? Now, cloning has reemerged with as
vengeance as scientists at the University of Hawaii report today in
the journal Nature that they have created not one but 22 animals
that are clones of adult mice. Seven of them, in fact, are clones
of clones, they say. By Gina Kolata.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NEW YORK &LR;  (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   NY-SCAFFOLD-COLLAPSE (New York) _ Ledeall on the aftermath of
the collapse of a scaffold at at Times Square construction site. By
Dan Barry.
</P>
