   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-PEOPLE (Tokyo) -- With the highest unemployment since
World War II, laid-off workers can't find work. People are saving
rather than spending, fueling deflation and stagnation. By Indira
A.R. Lakshmanan. 1400 words.
</P>
<P>
   CANADA-HERD (Halifax, N.S.) _ The future of wild horses on an
island off Nova Scotia is debated as a study suggests the herd is
devouring the sea grass that holds the island together. By Colin
Nickerson. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
