   TALL-SHIP (Salem, Mass.) -- A replica of the merchant ships that
made Salem rich two centuries ago is scheduled for launching. But
even though the ship was built to sail, it seems destined to sit at
a Salem pier. By David Arnold. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   GOOD-NEWS-GARAGE (Burlington, Vt.) -- Lutheran churches solve
one of the most difficult barriers facing poor folks _ a lack of
transportation. By Diego Ribadeneira. 1100 words.
</P>
