<P>
   TECH-PROMISES _ AUSTIN _ Technology is famous for breaking its
promises.
</P>
<P>
   Two years ago ``the next big thing'' was network computers: They
would would cost less than $500 and have no hard drive. Instead,
the network computer would keep all of its information on the
Internet. To retrieve a document or game, you had to be online.
Twenty-four months later, the idea lies in the technology
graveyard, along with virtual reality glasses and long distance
over the Internet. (Kallenberg, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
