<P>
   SENATE-JONES (Washington) -- Committee rejects the nomination of
Florida state senator Daryl Jones to become secretary of the Air
Force because of questions over his flying record and veracity. By
Bob Hohler. 1150 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ALZHEIMERS-GENES (Undated) -- Two new genetic discoveries are
helping to fill in the missing pieces of the Alzheimer's puzzle.
Once gene may determine whether someone will get late-onset
Alzheimer's, while another appears to determine when it will arise.
By Richard A. Knox. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   CLONES-MICE (New York) -- Erasing lingering doubts about
science's ability to clone mammals, researchers have made the first
identical copies of adult mice, and also have confirmed that Dolly
the lamb is a genuine clone. By Richard Saltus. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   OBITUARY-SHEPARD (Undated) -- Alan Shepard, the first American
in space and the first human to play golf on the moon, is dead at
74. By David L. Chanlder. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-YOUNG-DRIVERS (Boston) -- A bill expected to signed into law
next week will make it tougher for young people to get driving
licenses and impose new driving restrictions once they do. By Steve
Kiehl. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
