over the often lonely and expensive prospect of boat ownership, a
growing number of sailors are joining sailing clubs. The
organizations _ about a dozen from Newport Harbor to Santa Barbara
_ serve as both sailing certification centers and as intermediaries
between boatless sailors who pay monthly dues and charter fees and
boat owners willing to lease out their boats to offset costs. &QL; 
By Jeremy Bagott. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.)
