   &QL; 
OUT-ALBACORE (Los Angeles) _ This angler was fairly champing at the
bit to get out albacore fishing after the long-finned tuna had been
caught in large numbers up and down the coast in recent weeks. But
as with many open water fish, finding them is the biggest battle.
On this trip they were never found and coming back skunked after
what amounted to a 29-hour boat ride never felt worse. &QL; 
By Brett Pauly. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) &QL;
</P>
