<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BRAVES-ONDECK23-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On Deck: Philadelphia Phillies
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 7:35 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Veterans Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   TV/radio: WUPA, 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: RHP Kevin Millwood (10-5, 4.30; 2-0,
1.80 lifetime vs. Phillies) vs. RHP Tyler Green (6-6, 4.71; 3-0,
3.12 lifetime vs. Atlanta).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Millwood has lost three of his last four starts, dating
back to a seven-run shelling by Montreal on June 19. He may have
deserved better in his last outing, a 7-1 loss to Milwaukee and
Steve Woodard. Millwood was accountable for just three of those
runs over six innings, although three doubles and a home run were
included in the eight hits he allowed. He faced the Phillies in his
first start of the season, and although he left the game after five
innings with a 3-1 lead, he did not factor in the decision. Green
has become an Atlanta nemesis. He faced them twice in April, went
1-0, gave up two runs in 10 innings and left a shrugging Bobby Cox
saying: ``Hey, he's improved.'' Those two games were as good as
Green has had all season. He is 0-2 since the All-Star break and
was beaten 7-0 by the New York Mets in his last outing, when Mike
Piazza hit two home runs. Javy Lopez has a career .385 average
against Green.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
