   TANKERS-OIL (Undated) Increasingly anxious at the danger of a
winter oil spill, Gov. Gary Locke and Sen. Patty Murray are
pressing the Clinton administration to immediately require tug
escorts for oil-laden tankers entering the Strait of Juan de Fuca.
In a letter to Vice President Al Gore, Locke also urged Gore to
support the addition of rescue tugs near Neah Bay and the San Juan
Islands. The Clinton administration says it will soon announce new
tanker safety measures. But a top White House aide indicated it
would be difficult to put in a tug escort requirement by this
winter.
