<P>
   (NYT23) WASHINGTON -- July 22, 1998 -- LABOR-BOARD-B&AMP;W, 7-22 --
Although his term as head the National Labor Relations Board is not
up until Aug. 27, William Gould IV recently left Washington to
return to California. Gould, 62, originally said he hoped he would
be remembered for pushing the board back toward the center after
its rightward swing in the Reagan-Bush years. But he is more likely
to be remembered for warring with Congress. (Stephen Crowley/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) WASHINGTON -- July 22, 1998 -- ENERGY-CONFIRM, 7-22 --
Bill Richardson, left, the chief United States delegate to the
