<P>
   (NYT21) NEW YORK -- July 22, 1998 -- NY-SCAFFOLD-IMPACT, 7-22 --
Times Square is relatively empty Wednesday. The collapse of an
elevator tower Tuesday at a construction site here continued to
disrupt the routine of midtown Manhattan, as dozens of local shops
remained shuttered, hundreds of police officers directed traffic
away from blocked-off streets and multitudes of tourists and
workers marveled, muttered - and adapted. (J. Emilio Flores/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT20) NEW YORK -- July 22, 1998 -- JETT-SEC, 7-22 -- An
administrative law judge found Joseph Jett, a former Kidder trader,
guilty Tuesday of false record-keeping in a civil case brought by
the SEC. Jett, who is black, claims that securities cases similar
to his have resulted in much lesser penalties. ``When all things
are equal and the only difference is color, I have to wonder,'' he
says. ``The laws that are supposed to treat all men equally don't
seem to be doing the job.'' (Fred R. Conrad/New York Times Photo)
</P>
